27/03/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- One of Turkey's most beloved artists, singer Ibrahim Tatilises, was released from intensive care on Friday (March 25th). 
Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan visited the singer Friday at the Istanbul hospital. 
He is doing much better and will start physical therapy, Erdogan said after the meeting. 
The prime minister also announced he had accepted Tatilises' application to run as a candidate for the Justice and Development Party (AKP) in the upcoming June 12th general elections.
Tatilises was shot in the head in an assassination attempt on March 14th and has undergone life-saving treatment. 
(Zaman - 26/03/11; World Bulletin - 25/03/11)
